(1/3) DCHHS has received questions about how we report #COVID cases. Here are the key takeaways: 1. DCHHS only reports positive PCR test results. DCHHS does not include antibody test results in our daily COVID cases.
(2/3) 2. DCHHS does not report “probable” COVID cases. Only cases confirmed by a PCR test are reported.

(3/3) 3. If an individual receives multiple COVID tests, DCHHS only reports 1 positive case for that individual. DCHHS uses software to identify people who have received multiple tests (by matching name and birthday) and will eliminate any repeat results from our daily reports.
